{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17538547","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17538547"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T17:29:18+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T17:29:18+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16215"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"16215","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/16215"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.12,0.02,0.36,0.05,0.44]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8906"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"64365"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"8906","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/8906"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16215"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"49797"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"22"},{"type":"tags","id":"23"},{"type":"tags","id":"66"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"4168"},{"type":"tags","id":"4169"},{"type":"tags","id":"4540"},{"type":"tags","id":"4980"},{"type":"tags","id":"10948"},{"type":"tags","id":"10949"},{"type":"tags","id":"11634"},{"type":"tags","id":"12802"},{"type":"tags","id":"12963"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"21195"},{"type":"contributions","id":"35971"},{"type":"contributions","id":"39785"},{"type":"contributions","id":"41666"},{"type":"contributions","id":"43621"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"64365","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/64365"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 34-year-old woman presents to the General Practice clinic with her partner for fertility assessment. They have been trying to conceive for two years without success. She has irregular menstrual cycles and a history of endometriosis. She has no other medical history and takes no regular medications. Her partner is 36 years old with no medical history. Investigations reveal the woman has bilateral tubal blockage on hysterosalpingogram. Her partner\u0027s semen analysis shows sperm count 8 million/mL (\u0026gt;15), motility 15% (\u0026gt;32%), and normal morphology 2% (\u0026gt;4%).\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most appropriate assisted reproductive technique?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Intrauterine insemination","Gamete intrafallopian transfer","Intracytoplasmic sperm injection","Zygote intrafallopian transfer","Standard in vitro fertilisation"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis couple presents with both female factor (tubal blockage, endometriosis) and severe male factor infertility. The key to management is recognising that the sperm parameters are significantly abnormal across all measures, showing oligoasthenoteratozoospermia.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EIntracytoplasmic sperm injection\u003C/strong\u003E is most appropriate as the sperm parameters show severe male factor infertility with low count, poor motility, and abnormal morphology. ICSI bypasses these deficiencies by directly injecting a single sperm into each egg.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EStandard in vitro fertilisation\u003C/strong\u003E would be less likely to succeed given the severe male factor infertility. With such poor sperm parameters, the chances of successful fertilisation through conventional insemination would be very low.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EIntrauterine insemination\u003C/strong\u003E would not be appropriate due to both the bilateral tubal blockage and the poor sperm parameters. The combination of these factors would make successful conception extremely unlikely.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EGamete intrafallopian transfer\u003C/strong\u003E and \u003Cstrong\u003Ezygote intrafallopian transfer\u003C/strong\u003E are older techniques that require at least one patent fallopian tube and are rarely used in modern practice. They would not be appropriate given this patient\u0027s bilateral tubal blockage.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe presence of both severe male factor infertility and female factor infertility makes ICSI the clear choice in this case. The technique compensates for poor sperm parameters by selecting individual sperm for injection, while the IVF component addresses the tubal factor.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Intracytoplasmic sperm injection (ICSI) is indicated when there is severe male factor infertility or previous failed IVF cycles.","Standard IVF is appropriate for female factor infertility with normal sperm parameters.","Severe oligoasthenoteratozoospermia (low count, motility, and morphology) is a clear indication for ICSI."],"references":["Rosenwaks Z, Pereira N. The pioneering of intracytoplasmic sperm injection: historical perspectives. Reproduction. 2017 Dec;154(6):F71-F77. doi: 10.1530/REP-17-0308. Epub 2017 Oct 18. PMID: 29046342.","Choe J, Shanks AL. In vitro fertilization [Internet]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2023 [cited 2024 Nov 22]. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK562266/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"49797"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16215"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"49797","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/49797"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-11-23T14:14:18+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-11-23T14:15:08+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8906"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions"